The paper deals with the wiretap model of secure communication, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses the concept of perfect secrecy and reliability, which are important in cryptography (cs.CR). The paper proposes a new model for wiretap adversaries, which involves modifying the sent codeword, and this is related to error-correcting codes (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the security and efficiency properties of the proposed code family, which is related to system security (cs.SI) and network security (cs.NI).
